 MBOMBELA – A camping trip took a turn for the worse when a Land Rover caught fire on the Schoemanskloof Pass. The incident apparently happened today around lunch time. A video of the incident recently surfaced. The driver of the vehicle stood helplessly, witnessing his Land Rover Discovery being engulfed in flames. He said in the video that while driving uphill, he received a “Performance Lost” error on his dashboard before the vehicle burst into flames. Here is a video taken by Lida van Huyssteen shortly after the incident, which took place on Patatanek, Schoemaskloof around 13:00.  Also read: BREAKING NEWS: Accident on Robber’s Pass claims young biker’s life 